        <updateDate>2017-02-01T15:13:25Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Honoring Emergency Response Officers Benefits Reform Act of 2016 or the HERO Benefits Reform Act of 2016</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Omnibus Crime Control and Safe Streets Act of 1968 to establish, with respect to a public safety officer's death benefits, a rebuttable presumption that: (1) the officer acted properly at the time of injury or death, and (2) specified limitations on the officer's benefits do not apply.</p> <p>The&nbsp;bill also extends such benefits to fire police officers and fire investigators.</p> <p>In addition, with respect to an appeal of a determination to deny such benefits, the bill: (1) specifies that the standard of review shall be <em>de novo</em> (without deference to the determination), and (2) establishes certain exceptions to administrative exhaustion limitations.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
